<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-24T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-24T18:00:00-05:00" n="411" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d411">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1163 Am 3/225: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-24T19:00:00-04:00">September 24, 1937—7
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>263. Your 707, September 23, 2 p.m.<note n="65" xml:id="d411fn65">Not
                                printed.</note> On September 23 the Department instructed Tokyo to
                            make appropriate representations in regard to the endangering of the
                            American personnel of the mission<note n="66" xml:id="d411fn66">Precious
                                Blood Monastery.</note> and on the same day authorized Tientsin to
                            confirm in writing its oral protest to the Japanese Consul General.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>